<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-16T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">845.01/272: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-16T14:00:00-04:00">June
                                        16, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>427. The President desires that his letter to Gandhi (your 357, May
                                19) be delivered, after you have appropriately advised the
                                Government of India. You may wish to utilize Gandhi’s son as an
                                intermediary for delivery.</p>
                            <p>Appropriate explanations regarding the delay will of course be in
                                order.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>